  "prompt": "What are the good game stalls ideas that which gives much money than others at college fests?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are some game stall ideas for college fests that typically attract a lot of participants and can generate good revenue:\n\n1. **Escape Room**: Create a themed escape room with puzzles and challenges that teams need to solve within a time limit. This can be highly engaging and participants are often willing to pay a premium for the experience.\n\n2. **Carnival Games**: Classic games like ring toss, balloon darts, and bean bag toss are always popular. These games are simple, quick, and can be set up with inexpensive materials while charging per play.\n\n3. **Trivia Contest**: Organize a trivia contest with categories like pop culture, sports, history, and college-specific knowledge. Charge an entry fee and offer attractive prizes for winners.\n\n4. **Virtual Reality (VR) Experiences**: Set up VR stations with popular games or immersive experiences. This technology is highly appealing, and people are often willing to pay for the unique experience.\n\n5. **Minute to Win It**: Host a series of quick, fun challenges inspired by the TV show \"Minute to Win It.\" Charge an entry fee and offer prizes for those who complete the tasks within the time limit.\n\n6. **Photo Booth with Props**: Create a themed photo booth with fun props and backgrounds. Charge for individual or group photos and offer instant printouts or digital copies.\n\n7. **Laser Tag or Nerf Wars**: Set up an arena for laser tag or Nerf gun battles. These activities are highly interactive and competitive, attracting large groups willing to pay for the thrill.\n\n8. **Football/Soccer Penalty Shootout**: Set up a goalpost and charge participants to take penalty shots. Offer prizes for those who score the most goals.\n\n9. **Mystery Box Challenge**: Create boxes with hidden items inside and charge participants to guess the contents by feeling through a hole. Offer prizes for correct guesses.\n\n10. **Spin the Wheel**: Have a spinning wheel with various prizes and charge participants to spin. The chance to win something exciting can draw a lot of people.\n\n11. **Gaming Tournament**: Organize tournaments for popular video games like FIFA, Call of Duty, or Super Smash Bros. Charge an entry fee and offer cash prizes or merchandise for winners.\n\n12. **Bubble Soccer**: Rent inflatable bubble suits and organize soccer matches. Participants pay to join in the fun and chaotic games.\n\nRemember to promote your stalls effectively, offer appealing prizes, and ensure that the games are fair and enjoyable. Engaging and interactive experiences tend to attract more participants and generate higher revenue.",
